author: Professor Stewart Cole
name: tuberculist
notes:
The most complete H37Rv genome, manually annotated.

Different from the french <http://genolist.pasteur.fr/TubercuList/> which is not up-to-date.

However, both genomes are much better than the one in UniProt, which is also mixed with CD1551, according to their help desk.

Swiss TubercuList in numbers:
  - 4,411,532 bp of DNA sequence representing the whole Mycobacterium tuberculosis chromosome (strain H37Rv, EMBL/GenBank/DDBJ entry AL123456)
  - 4,011 protein genes
  - 7 pseudogenes
  - 45 tRNA genes
  - 3 rRNA genes
  - 2 stable RNA genes
  - 9 sRNA genes
  - Gene density: 1,099 bases per gene
  - Average gene length: 1,004 bases per gene
  - Protein coding (CDS) bases: 4,028,175
  - Protein coding percentage: 91.3%
  - GC percentage: 65.61 %
title: TubercuList - Mycobacterium Tuberculosis Database
